ZL}}\n|}\n\n==== 6th place play-off ====\n{| style=\"width:70%;\" cellspacing=\"1\"\n|-\n!width=35%| !!width=15%|\n!\n|-\n| 6 February 2016\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|{{fl-rt|NZL}}||align=center|3 \u2013 '''4'''||'''{{flb|MAS}}'''\n|}\n\n==== Semi-finals ====\n{| style=\"width:70%;\" cellspacing=\"1\"\n|-\n!width=35%| !!width=15%|\n!\n|-\n| 5 February 2016\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|{{fl-rt|THA}}||align=center|2 \u2013 '''5'''||'''{{flb|SIN}}'''\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|{{fl-rt|JPN}}||align=center|2 \u2013 '''4'''||'''{{flb|AUS}}'''\n|}\n\n==== Bronze medal game ====\n{| style=\"width:70%;\" cellspacing=\"1\"\n|-\n!width=35%| !!width=15%|\n!\n|-\n| 6 February 2016\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|{{fl-rt|JPN}}||align=center|1 \u2013 '''6'''||'''{{flb|THA}}'''\n|}\n\n==== Final ====\n{| style=\"width:70%;\" cellspacing=\"1\"\n|-\n!width=35%| !!width=15%|\n!\n|-\n| 6 February 2016\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''{{fl-rt|AUS}}'''||align=center|'''5''' \u2013 2||{{flb|SIN}}\n|}\n\n===Final ranking===\n<onlyinclude>{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Rank\n!Team\n|-bgcolor=BBF3BB\n|align=center|{{gold01}}||{{flb|AUS}}\n|-bgcolor=BBF3BB\n|align=center|{{silver02}}||{{flb|SIN}}\n|-bgcolor=BBF3BB\n|align=center|{{bronze03}}||{{flb|THA}}\n|-\n|align=center|4||{{flb|JPN}}\n|-\n|align=center|5||{{flb|KOR}}\n|-\n|align=center|6||{{flb|MAS}}\n|-\n|align=center|7||{{flb|NZL}}\n|}\n\n{{legend|#BBF3BB|Qualified for the [[2016 Men's World Floorball Championships]].}}</onlyinclude>\n\n==Americas==\nThe qualification rules are as follows:\n* The two best teams from the qualification group will qualify\n'''Dates:''' 12 \u2013 14 February 2016<ref name=\"Americas Qualification\">{{cite web\n | url = http://www.floorball.org/pages/EN/Mens-WFCQ-2016-AMER-USA\n | title = Men's World Championships 2016 Qualifications \u2013 Americas Qualification\n | date = 26 January 2016\n | website = www.floorball.org\n | publisher = [[International Floorball Federat