016. A total of 33 teams<ref name=\"General schedule\">{{cite web\n | url = http://www.floorball.org/news.asp?alue=775&id_tiedote=4602\n | title = Men\u00b4s WFC 2016 Qualification match schedules \u2013 16.10.2015\n | date = 16 October 2015\n | website = www.floorball.org\n | publisher = [[International Floorball Federation]]\n | access-date = 12 January 2016}}</ref> competed for fifteen spots. The final tournament was organized by [[Latvia]] in December 2016.\n\n==Overview==\nNumbers in brackets show the ranking before the qualification started, which is based on results from the last two World Championships.<ref name=\"General schedule\" />\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!width=17%| '''Europe 1'''\n!width=17%| '''Europe 2'''\n!width=17%| '''Europe 3'''\n!width=17%| '''Europe 4'''\n!width=17%| '''Asia/Oceania'''\n!width=17%| '''Americas'''\n|-\n|valign=top|\n{{flb|SWE}} (1)<br />\n{{flb|SVK}} (9)<br />\n{{flb|RUS}} (11)<br />\n{{flb|BEL}} (24)<br />\n{{flb|FRA}} (25)<br />\n{{flb|ISL}} (\u2013)\n|valign=top|\n{{flb|FIN}} (2)<br />\n{{flb|EST}} (8)<br />\n{{flb|DEN}} (12)<br />\n{{flb|AUT}} (22)<br />\n{{flb|NED}} (28)\n|valign=top|\n{{flb|SUI}} (3)<br />\n{{flb|GER}} (7)<br />\n{{flb|POL}} (14)<br />\n{{flb|ESP}} (22)<br />\n{{flb|GBR}} (29)<br />\n{{flb|GEO}} (38)\n|valign=top|\n{{flb|CZE}} (4)<br />\n{{flb|NOR}} (6)<br />\n{{flb|SRB}} (20)<br />\n{{flb|ITA}} (21)<br />\n{{flb|SLO}} (27)<br />\n{{flb|LIE}} (30)\n|valign=top|\n{{flb|JPN}} (15)<br />\n{{flb|AUS}} (16)<br />\n{{flb|KOR}} (17)<br />\n{{flb|SIN}} (18)<br />\n{{flb|NZL}} (26)<br />\n{{flb|MYS}} (33)<br />\n{{flb|THA}} (\u2013)<br />\n|valign=top|\n{{flb|USA}} (10)<br />\n{{flb|CAN}} (13)<br />\n{{flb|JAM}} (32)\n|}\n\n==Europe==\nThe qualification rules are as follows:\n* The two best teams from each qualification group will qualify\n* The two best third placed teams will qualify\n** The calculation of the best 3rd teams will follow this order:\n*** 1. Average number of points \n*** 2. Average goal difference \n*** 3. Average scored goals\n*** 4. Drawing of lots\n\n===European Qualification 1===\n'''Dates:''' 3 \u2013 7 February 2016<ref name=\"European Qualification 1\">{{cite web\n | url = http://www.floorball.org/pages/EN/Mens-WFCQ-2016-EUR1-Slovakia\n | title = Men's World Championships 2016 Qualifications \u2013 European Qualification 1\n | date = 5 February 2016\n | website = www.floorball.org\n | publisher = [[International Floorball Federation]]\n | access-date = 6 February 2016}}</ref><br>\n'''Venue:''' [[Arena Klokocina]], [[Nitra]], [[Slovakia]]\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!width=\"165\"|Team\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| Pld | Played}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| W | Won}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| D | Drawn}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| L | Lost}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| GF | Goals for}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| GA | Goals against}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| GD | Goal difference}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| Pts | Points}}\n!width=\"376\"|Status\n|- bgcolor=#ACE1AF\n|align=\"left\"|{{flb|SWE}}\n|5||5||0||0||106||7||+99||10||rowspan=2|Qualify for the 2016 Men's World Floorball Championships\n|- bgcolor=#ACE1AF\n|align=\"left\"|{{flb|SVK}}\n|5||4||0||1||50||31||+19||8\n|- bgcolor=#CCCCFF\n|align=\"left\"|{{flb|RUS}}\n|5||3||0||2||43||33||+10||6||Referred to the ranking of third-placed teams\n|- bgcolor=#FF8888\n|align=\"left\"|{{flb|BEL}}\n|5||2||0||3||23||56||\u201333||4||rowspan=3|Miss out on the 2016 Men's World Floorball Championships\n|- bgcolor=#FF8888\n|align=\"left\"|{{flb|ISL}}\n|5||1||0||4||19||67||\u201348||2\n|- bgcolor=#FF8888\n|align=\"left\"|{{flb|FRA}}\n|5||0||0||5||13||60||\u201347||0\n|}\n\n{| style=\"width:70%;\" cellspacing=\"1\"\n|-\n!width=35%|\n!width=15%|\n!\n|-\n| 3 February 2016\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''{{fl-rt|SWE}}'''||align=center|'''22''' \u2013 0||{{flb|BEL}}\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|{{fl-rt|ISL}}||align=center|6 \u2013 '''12'''||'''{{flb|RUS}}'''\n|-